cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CY 

The paper involves the use of crowdsourcing to identify polyp-free segments in virtual colonoscopy videos, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques to reconstruct 3D colon models and identify polyps, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper discusses the need to reduce reading time for radiologists. Multimedia (cs.MM) is relevant as the paper involves the use of videos for crowd evaluation. Cybernetics (cs.CY) is also relevant as the paper involves the use of collective intelligence of non-expert workers.
